relative to fair point/reduced-neuron baselines.\"\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:29:  baseline_definitions:\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:30:    P0: Canonical point baseline using passive leaky linear non-spiking single-compartment neurons matched to the same connectome slice and readout.\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:31:    P1: Stronger reduced baseline using an effective-point or reduced-compartment model with explicit synaptic integration current or explicit delay structure.\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:40:    - id: m1_survives_stronger_baseline\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:41:      statement: Survival against the stronger reduced baseline P1.\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:56:    comparison: surface_wave/intact versus matched baseline/intact, with the intact-minus-baseline gap contrasted against the shuffled condition\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:57:    expected_relationship: The surface-wave model produces a small but reproducible shared-output departure relative to the matched baseline.\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:60:      - same stimulus\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:61:      - shared downstream readout\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:65:    notes: Optimize Milestone 1 around null-direction suppression rather than headline task accuracy.\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:75:    comparison: surface_wave/intact versus matched baseline/intact, then intact versus shuffled\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:79:      - same stimulus\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:96:    comparison: (surface_wave/intact - baseline/intact) versus (surface_wave/shuffled - baseline/shuffled)\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:101:      - matched baseline arm\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:104:    notes: This is the clearest falsifiability check for Milestone 1.\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:105:  - id: m1_survives_stronger_baseline\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:106:    name: Survival against stronger reduced baseline P1\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:107:    description: Confirm that the shared-output effect is not explained away by a stronger reduced baseline with explicit integration current or delay structure.\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:115:    comparison: surface_wave/intact versus baseline P1/intact, with the same comparison available under shuffled topology\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:116:    expected_relationship: The Milestone 1 effect remains detectable against P1, not only against P0.\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:118:      - baseline P1 arm\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:122:    notes: No numeric margin is locked yet; only the requirement that the effect survive the stronger reduced baseline.\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:138:      - same stimulus family\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:145:    - id: stimulus_setup\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:150:      description: Show point baseline and surface-wave model side by side on the same T4/T5-centered circuit.\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:162:  - id: stimulus_overview\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:164:    description: Simple moving-edge stimulus shown on the chosen retinotopic patch.\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:165:    artifact_name: ui/stimulus_overview.json\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:166:  - id: surface_vs_baseline_split_view\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:168:    description: Side-by-side view of scalar baseline activity and distributed surface state for the same circuit and stimulus.\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:169:    artifact_name: ui/surface_vs_baseline_split_view.json\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:172:    description: Overlay of shared output traces for the matched surface-wave and baseline conditions.\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:186:  - id: baseline_challenge_comparison\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:188:    description: P0 versus P1 baseline challenge plot for the same observable family.\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:189:    artifact_name: plots/baseline_challenge_comparison.png\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:192:    description: Final panel summarizing the four-part Milestone 1 decision rule.\nconfig/milestone_6_verification.yaml:14:  processed_coupling_dir: data/processed/milestone_6_verification/coupling\nconfig/milestone_6_verification.yaml:16:  manifest_json: data/processed/milestone_6_verification/asset_manifest.json\nconfig/milestone_7_verification.yaml:18:  processed_coupling_dir: data/processed/milestone_7_verification/coupling\nconfig/milestone_7_verification.yaml:19:  coupling_inspection_dir: data/processed/milestone_7_verification/coupling_inspection\nconfig/milestone_7_verification.yaml:20:  manifest_json: data/processed/milestone_7_verification/asset_manifest.json\nconfig/milestone_7_verification.yaml:62:  coupling_assembly:\nconfig/milestone_7_verification.yaml:63:    version: coupling_assembly.v1\nconfig/milestone_7_verification.yaml:69:      version: coupling_delay_model.v1\nscripts/setup_flywire_token.py:66:    result: list[str] = []\nscripts/setup_flywire_token.py:71:                result.append(new_line)\nscripts/setup_flywire_token.py:74:        result.append(line)\nscripts/setup_flywire_token.py:77:        if result and result[-1] != \"\":\nscripts/setup_flywire_token.py:78:            result.append(\"\")\nscripts/setup_flywire_token.py:79:        result.append(new_line)\nscripts/setup_flywire_token.py:82:    env_file.write_text(\"\\n\".join(result).rstrip() + \"\\n\", encoding=\"utf-8\")\nconfig/milestone_8b_verification.yaml:2:  processed_stimulus_dir: data/processed/milestone_8b_verification/stimuli\nconfig/milestone_8b_verification.yaml:6:  manifest_path: manifests/examples/milestone_1_demo.yaml\nconfig/milestone_8b_verification.yaml:7:  schema_path: schemas/milestone_1_experiment_manifest.schema.json\nconfig/milestone_8b_verification.yaml:10:  stimulus:\nconfig/milestone_