 |\ndocs/milestones.md:101:| 15 | Build experiment orchestration and ablations | Programming-heavy (80/20) | Jack lead | Batch runs, manifests, comparisons |\ndocs/milestones.md:111:## **Milestone 1 — Freeze the scientific claim, demo claim, and output contract**\ndocs/milestones.md:115: **Why it matters:** This prevents the project from becoming a cool visualization with no testable point, and locks the Milestone 1 scientific and artifact contract before the simulator is overbuilt.\ndocs/milestones.md:121:### **Milestone 1 operational claim**\ndocs/milestones.md:123:**In a connectome-constrained Drosophila visual motion circuit, adding a morphology-resolved surface state should produce small but reproducible, geometry-dependent departures in shared circuit observables relative to fair point/reduced-neuron baselines.**\ndocs/milestones.md:125:Milestone 1 is about **detectability, distinctness, and falsifiability of a small effect**.  \ndocs/milestones.md:133:* a shared downstream readout so comparison to baselines stays fair\ndocs/milestones.md:140:* a decoder or readout unavailable to the baselines  \ndocs/milestones.md:145:* **`P0`**: canonical point baseline using passive leaky linear non-spiking single-compartment neurons matched to the same circuit and readout  \ndocs/milestones.md:146:* **`P1`**: stronger reduced baseline using an effective-point or reduced-compartment model with explicit synaptic integration current or explicit delay structure\ndocs/milestones.md:151: In a connectome-constrained Drosophila visual motion circuit, adding a morphology-resolved surface state should produce small but reproducible, geometry-dependent departures in shared circuit observables relative to fair point/reduced-neuron baselines.\ndocs/milestones.md:153:**What should the wave model do differently than a baseline point-neuron model?**  \ndocs/milestones.md:154: It should add distributed, morphology-bound intraneuronal state and nothing else that can trivially explain the result.\ndocs/milestones.md:157: A geometry-sensitive shared-output effect, preferably on null-direction suppression or response latency, that survives a stronger reduced baseline.\ndocs/milestones.md:160: The same stimulus driving the same circuit in two models, producing a small but real output difference that shrinks or disappears when geometry is shuffled.\ndocs/milestones.md:167:* **Secondary shared readout:** direction selectivity index\ndocs/milestones.md:172:* **Moderate:** the surface model changes a shared readout such as null-direction suppression, latency, or DSI  \ndocs/milestones.md:173:* **Strong:** the shared-readout change shrinks or disappears when morphology or synapse topology is shuffled  \ndocs/milestones.md:174:* **Very strong:** the effect survives the stronger reduced baseline `P1`\ndocs/milestones.md:179:2. **`10–25 s`**: split screen with matched point baseline on the left and surface model on the right for the same T4/T5-centered circuit  \ndocs/milestones.md:186:* stimulus overview for the simple moving-edge input  \ndocs/milestones.md:187:* split view showing baseline scalar activity versus surface-state activity on morphology  \ndocs/milestones.md:188:* shared output trace overlay for the same circuit and stimulus  \ndocs/milestones.md:192:* `P0` versus `P1` challenge-baseline comparison plot  \ndocs/milestones.md:202:* Milestone 2+ simulator build-out beyond what is required to lock the design and output contract\ndocs/milestones.md:208:* creating the experiment manifest schema  \ndocs/milestones.md:210:* defining the required plots, UI states, and result-bundle fields for Milestone 1 checkoff\ndocs/milestones.md:222:* defining the Milestone 1 decision rule and falsification logic\ndocs/milestones.md:228:* the narrower Milestone 1 operational claim is preserved  \ndocs/milestones.md:229:* `P0` and `P1` baseline definitions are explicit  \ndocs/milestones.md:236:  ### **Milestone 1 decision rule**\ndocs/milestones.md:238:Milestone 1 is successful only if all four hold:\ndocs/milestones.md:242:3. survival against a stronger reduced baseline  \ndocs/milestones.md:245:This version is much tighter than the current section because it keeps the roadmap tone, but now locks the real burden of proof instead of leaving Milestone 1 as a high-level placeholder.\ndocs/milestones.md:269:* **readout stop point:** T4a/T5a axon terminals in lobula plate layer 1\ndocs/milestones.md:271:Only the columns inside the selected stimulus footprint should be included, plus a **one-ring halo** so each active detector retains its local sampling neighborhood.\ndocs/milestones.md:286:* terminal readout at lobula plate layer 1\ndocs/milestones.md:293:* T4b, T5b, LPi candidates, and tangential-cell readout candidates  \ndocs/milestones.md:312:**T4a/T5a \\+ direct ON/OFF reduced inputs \\+ central patch \\+ terminal readout**\ndocs/milestones.md:322:* promote **LPi / downstream tangential-cell readout** only after a clear T4/T5-level effect is established  \ndocs/milestones.md:324:* add additional **T4/T5 direction layers** only after the first horizontal-axis result is secure\ndocs/milestones.md:329:* root ID manifests for active, candidate, and context graphs  \ndocs/milestones.md:341:* there is a named manifest for the locked boundary  \ndocs/milestones.md:381:- manifest validation  \ndocs/milestones.md:386:- flagging missing metadata needed for later coupling/model design\ndocs/milestones.md:392:- the same experiment can be reproduced from a manifest\ndocs/milestones.md:424:- exporting manifests and reports\ndocs/milestones.md:435:- each subset produces a manifest and stats file  \ndocs/milestones.md:527:## Milestone 7 — Map synapses and define inter-neuron coupling\ndocs/milestones.md:540:- whether coupling is:  \ndocs/milestones.md:552:- serializing coupling maps  \ndocs/milestones.md:553:- coupling inspection tools\ndocs/milestones.md:557:- defining coupling kernels  \ndocs/milestones.md:560:- determining whether coupling is instantaneous, filtered, nonlinear, etc.\ndocs/milestones.md:566:- coupling rules are configurable and versioned\ndocs/milestones.md:574:### Milestone 8A — Canonical stimulus library\ndocs/milestones.md:585:- expansion/contraction flow  \ndocs/milestones.md:591:- stimulus generation code  \ndocs/milestones.md:592:- parameterized stimulus configs  \ndocs/milestones.md:598:- making sure the stimulus set is scientifically meaningful  \ndocs/milestones.md:678:## Milestone 9 — Build the baseline non-wave simulator\ndocs/milestones.md:691:- `baseline`  \ndocs/milestones.md:692:- `surface_wave`\ndocs/milestones.md:705:- defining a fair baseline model  \ndocs/milestones.md:706:- making sure the baseline is not a strawman  \ndocs/milestones.md:707:- helping choose comparable state variables and readouts\ndocs/milestones.md:711:- the same experiment manifest runs in baseline mode  \ndocs/milestones.md:717:## Milestone 10 — Implement the surface-wave dynamics engine\ndocs/milestones.md:744:- hybrid field \\+ readout system\ndocs/milestones.md:771:## Milestone 11 — Add hybrid morphology classes\ndocs/milestones.md:791:- routing between coupling modes\ndocs/milestones.md:807:## Milestone 12 — Define readouts and task layer\ndocs/milestones.md:814:Turn simulation output into interpretable, quantitative results.\ndocs/milestones.md:830:- readout pipeline implementation  \ndocs/milestones.md:834:- experiment result packaging\ndocs/milestones.md:845:- every run emits a standard result bundle  \ndocs/milestones.md:847:- baseline vs wave comparisons are quantitative, not just visual\ndocs/milestones.md:851:## Milestone 13 — Build the validation ladder\ndocs/milestones.md:887:- reproducible differences between baseline and wave mode  \ndocs/milestones.md:911:## Milestone 14 — Build the UI and analysis dashboard\ndocs/milestones.md:934:- baseline vs wave comparison mode  \ndocs/milestones.md:951:## Milestone 15 — Build experiment orchestration and ablations\ndocs/milestones.md:969:- coupling mode  \ndocs/milestones.md:978:- no lateral coupling  \ndocs/milestones.md:988:- result indexing  \ndocs/milestones.md:996:- interpreting the results\ndocs/milestones.md:1000:- whole suites run from manifest files  \ndocs/milestones.md:1002:- results are easy to compare\ndocs/milestones.md:1006:## Milestone 16 — Polish the demo narrative and showcase mode\ndocs/milestones.md:1021:5. compare baseline and wave mode  \ndocs/milestones.md:1048:## Milestone 17 — Extend to whole-brain context views\ndocs/milestones.md:1062:- optional simplified downstream readout modules\ndocs/milestones.md:1092:- manifest schema\ndocs/milestones.md:1096:- Milestone 1  \ndocs/milestones.md:1129:### Phase 3 — Circuit coupling and inputs\ndocs/milestones.md:1135:- stimulus and scene system  \ndocs/milestones.md:1140:- coupling kernels  \ndocs/milestones.md:1156:- implementation-heavy parts of Milestone 10  \ndocs/milestones.md:1161:- model formulation for Milestone 10  \ndocs/milestones.md:1167:- same experiment runs in both baseline and wave mode\ndocs/milestones.md:1186:- result interpretation\ndocs/milestones.md:1199:2. one canonical visual stimulus family  \ndocs/milestones.md:1201:4. one baseline simulator  \ndocs/milestones.md:1211:## Suggested interface contracts between Jack and Grant\ndocs/milestones.md:1215:### 1\\. Subset manifest contract\ndocs/milestones.md:1221:- which scene/stimulus is used  \ndocs/milestones.md:1222:- which readouts are active\ndocs/milestones.md:1224:### 2\\. Operator contract\ndocs/milestones.md:1234:### 3\\. Wave model contract\ndocs/milestones.md:1250:### 4\\. Result bundle contract\ndocs/milestones.md:1256:- task readouts  \ndocs/milestones.md:1260:### 5\\. UI data contract\ndocs/milestones.md:1269:- comparison results\ndocs/milestones.md:1287:- keeping the operators and coupling scientifically honest  \ndocs/milestones.md:1300:1. Milestone 1  \ndocs/milestones.md:1308:9. Milestone 10  \ndocs/milestones.md:1309:10. Milestone 11  \ndocs/milestone